[src:gamma-beta-functions/beta-function] In mathematics, the **beta function**, also called the Euler integral of the first kind, is a special function that is closely related to the gamma function and to binomial coefficients.
[src:gamma-beta-functions/beta-function] The beta function was studied by Leonhard Euler and Adrien-Marie Legendre and was given its name by Jacques Binet; its symbol Β is a Greek capital beta.
[src:gamma-beta-functions/beta-function] A proof is given below in § Relationship to the gamma function.
[src:gamma-beta-functions/beta-function] The beta function is also closely related to binomial coefficients.
[src:gamma-beta-functions/beta-function] To derive this relation, write the product of two factorials as integrals.
