[src:gamma-beta-functions/beta-function] In SciPy, `special.betainc` computes the regularized incomplete beta function—which is, in fact, the cumulative beta distribution.
[src:gamma-beta-functions/beta-function] To get the actual incomplete beta function, one can multiply the result of `special.betainc` by the result returned by the corresponding `beta` function.
[src:gamma-beta-functions/beta-function] In Mathematica, `Beta[x, a, b]` and `BetaRegularized[x, a, b]` give $\mathrm {B} (x;\,a,b)$ and $I_{x}(a,b)$ , respectively.
